{"header":"<h1>Module type <code><span>Bookkeeping.S</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Soteria_std","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Effects","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Bookkeeping","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"S","href":"#","kind":"module-type"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>Module type of a bookkeeping</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> t</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>The type of the information tracked by the effect.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-arg\"><a href=\"#type-arg\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> arg</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>The type of the argument to the effect, if it needs to be tracked.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-with_\"><a href=\"#val-with_\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> with_ : <span><a href=\"#type-arg\">arg</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> * <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>with_ arg f</code> runs function <code>f</code> and handles effects raised by the functions of this module, and returns a pair of the result of <code>f</code> and the data tracked by the effect. This is to be used when the user wants to directly manage the data tracked by the effect.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-with_dumped\"><a href=\"#val-with_dumped\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> with_dumped : <span><a href=\"#type-arg\">arg</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>with_dumped arg f</code> runs function <code>f</code> and handles effects raised by the functions of this module, and dumps the resulting data to the file specified by the current (externally-defined) configuration if it is set, or ignores them otherwise (if configured to do so).</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-with_ignored\"><a href=\"#val-with_ignored\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> with_ignored : <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>with_ignored () f</code> runs function <code>f</code> and handles effects raised by the functions of this module, but ignores their effect. This is to be used when the user does not wish to pay the performance cost of tracking the effect.</p></div></div>"}